Naveen Kumar, Named First Accused In Gauri Lankesh Murder, Taken Into Custody By Karnataka Police

Naveen Kumar, Named First Accused In Gauri Lankesh Murder, Taken Into Custody By Karnataka Police

The Karnataka Police have arrested KT Naveen Kumar, whom they say is the first accused in the sensational Gauri Lankesh murder case.

Kumar, who was apprehended by the Karnataka Special Investigation Team (SIT) for questioning earlier this month was arrest on Friday.

BCCL

According to reports Kumar is the founder of an outfit called Hindu Yuva Sena and is close to Sanatan Sanstha, a right wing group which had earlier come under suspicion in the case.

The radical outfit has also been linked in Maharashtra to the shooting of rationalists Narendra Dabholkar and Govind Pansare.

Police suspect Kumar of having direct involvement or supplying arms to the assassins of Lankesh.

BCCL

The 55-year-old editor of Lankesh Patrike, a tabloid was a know critic of right wing groups which many believed made her a target.

She was shot dead by unidentified men on motorbike outside her residence on September 5.

BCCL

CCTV cameras installed at her residence captured two men wearing helmets speeding away from the scene after the shooting. According to reports Kumar is said to resemble one of the accused caught on camera, the day of the crime.

